President Joseph R. Biden has issued a memorandum delegating authority to the Secretary of State regarding the drawdown of defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. The Secretary of State is now authorized to direct the drawdown of up to $175 million under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The memorandum also instructs the publication of this delegation in the Federal Register.